cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper deals with predicting socioeconomic attributes of social media users using both network and language information. This falls under the domain of computational social science, which is covered by the cs.SOC sub-category. The use of language features for prediction suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of graph embeddings for network analysis suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
